TITLE: Implementing AvatarGroup in React using Fluent UI
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the AvatarGroup component to render a list of names as avatars. It uses the partitionAvatarGroupItems function to divide avatars into inline and overflow groups. The component requires an array of names and outputs an avatar layout. Limitations include needing predefined names and an existing React environment.
