TITLE: Theme Object and FluentProvider Usage
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how a theme object is structured and used with FluentProvider to inject CSS variables into the DOM. It showcases how components can then reference these CSS variables using makeStyles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/theme-tokens.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
// Theme object
const theme = {
  global: {
    color: {
      black: '#000' // token value defined for global.color.black
    }
  }
}

// Application root - creates a div, injects --global-color-black: #000 to its styles
<FluentProvider theme={theme}>
  <ThemedComponent />
</FluentProvider>

// Fluent UI Themed Component
const useStyles = makeStyles([[null,
  theme => ({
    color: theme.global.color.black // ...but value is a css variable reference: 'var(--global-color-black)'
  })
]]

const ThemedComponent = () => {
  const cls = useStyles({})
  return <div className={cls}>ThemedComponent</div>
}
```

