TITLE: Handling Layered Component Z-Indexing with PortalMountNodeProvider
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet addresses issues with z-index conflicts when using layered components from both v8 and v9. The PortalMountNodeProvider is used to specify a mount node, ensuring correct layering by overriding default DOM layering behavior. It requires obtaining a reference to the v8 layer host.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/apps/public-docsite-v9/src/Concepts/Migration/FromV8/Troubleshooting.stories.mdx#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { FluentProvider, PortalMountNodeProvider } from '@fluentui/react-components';

function App() {
  // Get a reference to the v8 layer host
  const mountNode = document.getElementById('fluent-default-layer-host');

  return (
    <FluentProvider>
      <PortalMountNodeProvider mountNode={mountNode}>{/* your components */}</PortalMountNodeProvider>
    </FluentProvider>
  );
}
```

