TITLE: Using Predefined Motions as Components
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to use predefined motions, both as objects and as components, created with the `createMotionComponent` factory. The `FadeEnterSlow` component is created from the `fade` motion object and used to animate a `div` element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/motion-definition-n-apis.md#2025-04-20_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: tsx
