TITLE: Implementing Text Component with Success Color in Dark Theme
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to create a Text component with success color styling for the dark theme using makeStyles from FluentUI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/react-components/react-text/library/docs/MIGRATION.md#2025-04-20_snippet_15

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles, Text } from '@fluentui/react-components';

const useStyles = makeStyles(theme => ({
  root: {
     color: 'rgb(146, 195, 83)'
  },
})

const MyComponent = () => {
    const styles = useStyles()

    return <Text className={styles.root}>{...}</Text>
}
```

