TITLE: Handling Input Component Shorthands in React
DESCRIPTION: Provides a solution for handling input elements in React, demonstrating a workaround for slots that must not have children (as in input elements). The code ensures continued rendering without children by modifying slot properties post-solution.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/slot-null-rendering.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export function Input(props) {
  const state = {
    components: {
      input: 'input',
    },
    input: resolveShorthand(props.input, {
      children: React.Fragment, // ðŸš¨ getSlots requires children
    }),
  };
  const { slots, slotProps } = getSlots(state, ['input']);
  delete slotProps.input.children; // ðŸš¨ input can't have children

  return (
    <slots.root {...slotProps.root}>
      <slots.input {...slotProps.input} />
    </slots.root>
  );
}
```

