TITLE: Defining Checkbox Types in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates a pattern where 'CheckboxCommons' defines necessary attributes for 'CheckboxState', with 'CheckboxProps' using 'Partial' to make them optional. This reflects another pattern before proposed API changes in Fluent UI.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/remove-commons.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export type CheckboxCommons = {
  // These are required in state (made optional in props)
  size: 'medium' | 'large';
};

export type CheckboxProps =
  // Things in CheckboxCommons are optional in props
  Partial<CheckboxCommons> &
    ComponentProps<CheckboxSlots> & {
      // maybe some other props here
    };

export type CheckboxState =
  // Commons are required in state
  CheckboxCommons &
    ComponentState<CheckboxSlots> & {
      // maybe some other state here
    };
```

