TITLE: Creating a State Manager with @fluentui/state in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a state manager using `@fluentui/state`. It defines the state and actions for an input component, and then uses `createManager` to create a manager instance. The manager is initialized with an initial state value of 'Hello world!'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/fluentui/state/README.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { createManager, ManagerFactory } from '@fluentui/state';

type InputState = { value: string };
type InputActions = { change: (value: string) => void };

const createInputManager: ManagerFactory<InputState, InputActions> = config =>
  createManager<InputState, InputActions>({
    ...config,
    actions: {
      change: (value: string) => () => ({ value }),
    },
    state: { value: '', ...config.state },
  });
const manager = createInputManager({ state: { value: 'Hello world!' } });
```

