TITLE: Implementing ResizeGroup with CacheKey Optimization
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use cacheKey to optimize performance by reducing unnecessary DOM measurements. The cacheKey helps skip redundant size calculations for data objects with similar structures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/react-examples/src/react/ResizeGroup/docs/ResizeGroupOverview.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Example of using cacheKey for performance optimization
const ResizeGroupWithCaching = () => {
  const initialData = {
    items: [...controlItems],
    cacheKey: controlItems.map(item => item.key).join('|')
  };

  const onReduceData = (data) => {
    const reducedItems = data.items.slice(0, -1);
    return {
      items: reducedItems,
      cacheKey: reducedItems.map(item => item.key).join('|')
    };
  };

  return (
    <ResizeGroup
      data={initialData}
      onReduceData={onReduceData}
      renderContent={(data) => data.items}
    />
  );
}
```

