TITLE: Exposing Z-Index Layers as a Named Map (Discarded)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet presents a discarded option for managing z-index values using a named map. The `ZIndexLayers` type defines the semantic layers, and the `zIndexes` object maps these layers to specific z-index values. This approach was considered but ultimately discarded due to limitations regarding partner overrides.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/z-index-handling.md#2025-04-20_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
