TITLE: Defining EventData and EventHandler for Consistent Typing
DESCRIPTION: This code introduces helper types, EventData and EventHandler, to centralize and standardize event handling across components. EventData is used to structure data with specific and generic events, while EventHandler enforces consistent usage of React.SyntheticEvent or Event as the first callback argument, enhancing flexibility and ensuring type safety.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/event-handlers-event-type.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
export type EventData<Type extends string, TEvent> =
  | { type: undefined; event: React.SyntheticEvent | Event }
  | { type: Type; event: TEvent };

export type EventHandler<TData extends EventData<string, unknown>> = (
  ev: React.SyntheticEvent | Event,
  data: TData,
) => void;
```

