TITLE: Overriding Context Values - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: An example showing how to override the context value conditionally. Emphasizes the necessity to re-compute the context value on state changes to ensure proper re-rendering of consumers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/docs/react-v9/contributing/rfcs/react-components/convergence/context-values.md#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
// ðŸ›  In this example I would like to override `size` based on a condition
function useSuperBazState(props) {
  const state = useBazState(props);

  // âŒ is broken because `state.contextValue.size` remains the same
  if (props.reallyBig) {
    state.size = 'xxl';
  }

  // âŒ is broken because `state.contextValue` is a stable object and will not trigger
  //     a rerender
  if (props.reallyBig) {
    state.size = 'xxl';
    state.contextValue.size = 'xxl';
  }

  // âœ… only this solution will work as expected
  state.size = 'xxl';
  state.contextValue = React.useMemo(
    () => ({
      ...contextValue,
      ...(props.reallyBig && { size: 'xxl' }),
    }),
    [state.contextValue, props.reallyBig],
  );
}
```

