TITLE: Stateful Class Component in React with Event Handler
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates a stateful class component in React with an event handler. It extends `AutoControlledComponent` for easier state management. The `handleClick` method logs a message to the console when the component is clicked, and this method is bound to the `onClick` event of the div element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/fluentui/add-a-feature.md#2025-04-20_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
export interface MyComponentProps {}

class MyComponent extends AutoControlledComponent<MyComponentProps> {
  handleClick = e => {
    console.log('Clicked my component!');
  };

  render() {
    return <div onClick={this.handleClick} />;
  }
}
```

