TITLE: Getting Git hash for React component webpack configuration
DESCRIPTION: A function that retrieves the current Git commit hash for labeling builds with a unique identifier. Uses child_process to execute Git commands and extract the commit hash.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/react-components/react-teaching-popover/stories/src/TeachingPopover/TeachingPopoverDescription.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
const execSync = require('child_process').execSync;
function getGitHash() {
  let stdout = '';
  try {
    stdout = execSync('git rev-parse --short HEAD', {
      cwd: process.cwd(),
      stdio: ['pipe', 'pipe', 'ignore'],
    }).toString();
  } catch (e) {
    // We're probably not in a git repo at all, maybe in a CI harness?
    stdout = '';
  }

  // Clean stdout from command execution
  const cleanedHash = stdout.trim().replace(/\r?\n|\r/g, '');
  return cleanedHash;
}
```

