TITLE: Creating Mutable State with useButton_unstable Hook in React
DESCRIPTION: Defines a custom hook that generates mutable state for a button component, allowing for user-defined props and accessibility features. It handles default properties and applies behaviors based on the component's rendered type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/fluentui/blob/master/packages/react-components/react-utilities/src/compose/README.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const useButton_unstable = (props, ref) => {
  const state = {
    // Default props
    role: 'button',
    // User props
    ...props,
    // Overrides
    ref,
  };

  // Apply button behaviors.
  if (state.as !== 'button' && state.as !== 'a') {
    state.tabIndex = 0;
  }

  return state;
};
```

